# Overflow/compare-match counts (ovf1/compA/ovf2) climb continuously and are
# too real-time-sensitive to assert an exact count for. OCR1A/OCR2A's direct
# PWM side effect on pins 9/11 is applied synchronously in setup() the moment
# the register is written, though, so that part is fully deterministic.
0.2, ASSERT, PIN, 9, 128
0.2, ASSERT, PIN, 11, 64
